The [[Collectivity of Saint Martin]] requires its residents to register their [[motor vehicle]]s and display '''[[vehicle registration plate]]s'''.<ref>http://www.worldlicenseplates.com/world/CA_MRTN.html</ref> Current plates are [[Vehicle_registration_plates_of_Europe#Format|European standard]] 520 mm × 110 mm, and use French stamping dies. The [[overseas France|overseas departments and territories of France]] have three-digit codes based on the numbering system for departments in France, starting with 97, which was originally the single code designating overseas territories.<ref>http://www.plateshack.com/y2k/France2/france2y2k.html</ref>
{|class="wikitable" |- !Image !First issued !Design !Slogan !Serial format !Serials issued !Notes |- |[[File:Saint Martin license plate 1993 series rear.jpg|150px]] |1993 | | | | | 97-1 signifies Guadeloupe and nearby French islands |- |[[File:Saint Martin license plate 2009 series.jpg|150px]] |2009 | | | | | |- |}
